history.content:
What is probably happening is a result of a design flaw in CalCentral (or more accurately a design flaw in the underlying Oracle system that CalCentral hasn't accounted for):

When you try to enroll, Oracle/PeopleSoft identifies all the reasons that you might not be able to enroll. If you can't enroll, for any of those reasons, it sends you a message with the 1st reasons which is almost always about time conflicts if there is one. It does this without checking whether allowing time conflicts is enabled. So, if you can't enroll because the class is full or because the class is set up only to allow English majors but you aren't an English major... it tells you it is because of time conflicts.

There is conflicting information about cs170 and time conflicts. I know course staff have said they will allow conflicts but on cal central it still says I have time conflicts between cs170 and my other class.
history.subject: CS170 Lecture time conflicts
